docs.lead_paragraph: THE unidentified American -- we find him everywhere where trouble is. Annually there are thousands of him in the morgues, taken dead from rivers, street accidents, railroad wrecks, what not; the mysterious wanderers who drift to our asylums, of one sort or another, principally our madhouses, would, if mustered in an open field, rival an army corps in numbers.
